# Twitter Guardrails (canonical: TWITTER_LOOP.md)

Whenever drafting ANY tweet, recap, or social copy for this project:

1. **Verify every number first.** Run `node scripts/socialRecords.mjs` (records)
   and `node scripts/socialBoard.mjs` (live board with time buckets). Never
   quote a W-L record, unit total, or pick that didn't come from these this
   session. Use the pick's `selection` field verbatim.
2. **Sound human.** Voice = `MY_VOICE_PROFILE.md`. Rotate post architecture
   (story / one-liner / desk note / question-first / ✅-recap) — never the same
   structure back-to-back. Banned: "let's dive in", "game-changer", "delve",
   default "tail or fade? 🎯" closers, 3-emoji rows.
3. **Sell without selling.** Canonical language + TONE RULE: `BRAND_MESSAGING.md`.
   Complete calm sentences — no fragment-stack swagger ("Every L public."), no
   self-conscious mantras. Offer = "the first week is free, grade it yourself";
   never prices or "sign up". Site link ONLY in a ~25-min self-reply, never
   tweet 1. No hashtags. Every draft names the site screenshot to attach.
4. **Prioritize top-tier picks inside 60 min of start.** Picks >60 min out MUST
   carry a natural line-movement reminder: sharp money moves, the site is the
   live truth, picks lock 15 min before start.
5. **Close on a real question** (2026 algo weights replies ~27x likes) and
   recommend a post window + first-30-min reply babysitting.
6. **Research with Firecrawl** (`FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` env secret,
   `https://api.firecrawl.dev/v2/search|/scrape`) for current viral formats
   before big posts; fold findings into `TWITTER_GROWTH_PLAYBOOK.md` (dated).
   **The X API is also live** (MCP server `user-xapi`, or
   `npx -y @xdevplatform/xurl <path>`; authed as @Real_NHL_Savant, user id
   1991513001204281345): use it for engagement truth, the mentions inbox, and
   recent-search reply targets. Credits are pay-per-use — be surgical.
7. **A day's output is a slate, not a tweet** (TWITTER_LOOP.md G7): hero +
   pre-written win/loss grade posts + 3–5 drafted replies under big accounts'
   live betting posts + one new-follower beat. Reply targets are found
   freshest-first (Firecrawl `site:x.com [event] bet`, `tbs:"qdr:n90"` → widen
   to `qdr:h3` → `qdr:d` last). ≤90-min posts get replies; aged-but-viral
   (100K+ views) get quote-tweets. Replies to big accounts are the #1
   out-of-network reach lever at our size.
8. **Target the scored actions** (`ALGO_PSYCH_PLAYBOOK.md` — ground truth from
   X's open-sourced ranker). Every hero names the 2–3 feed actions it's built
   to win (reply / follow_author / photo_expand / share_via_dm / dwell) as
   `algoActions`, passes the negative-signal audit (nothing that earns
   mute/not_interested — polarize the question, never attack a person), carries
   a follow-conversion beat (an open loop that makes following necessary),
   stays in-lane (embedding discipline), and sits ≥2–3h from our previous post
   (author-diversity attenuation).
9. **Log every posted tweet.** When the user says they posted (any phrasing +
   URL), immediately run `node scripts/socialLedger.mjs log --url <url>
   --draft <ready_to_post file> --pick <hero|altN>` (or explicit
   --structure/--mechanic tags for custom copy). Before writing new drafts,
   run `node scripts/socialLedger.mjs refresh` + `report` and let the
   structure/mechanic leaderboards pick the winning shape. Tag every draft
   candidate with structure/mechanic/refTag so logging works.

Full system + phases: `TWITTER_LOOP.md`. Drafts only — never post for the user.
